---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About Us"
	description="Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet"
	pubDate={new Date('August 08 2021')}
	heroImage="/me.jpg"
>
{% extends "base.html" %}

{% block title %}About | {{ site_name }}{% endblock %}
{% block meta_description %}The mission, editorial principles, corrections policy, and disclosure standards of {{ site_name }}.{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
<article class="prose-page">
  <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
  <h1>{{ site_name }}</h1>
  <p class="lead">{{ site_tagline }}</p>

  <h2>Editorial purpose</h2>
  <p>The publication is designed for work that benefits from context: current reporting, analysis, historical biographies, essays, primary-source material, and research papers. Every page should clearly identify its author, content type, publication date, and subsequent corrections.</p>

  <h2>Evidence and attribution</h2>
  <p>Historical and scholarly work should distinguish primary sources from later interpretation. Citations, bibliographies, image credits, archival references, and attached source documents are part of the publication record rather than decorative afterthoughts.</p>

  <h2>Corrections</h2>
  <p>Substantive corrections should remain visible on the article and include a date and explanation. Minor copy edits may be incorporated without a correction note when they do not alter the meaning of the work.</p>

  <h2>Editorial labels</h2>
  <p>News, analysis, opinion, history, interviews, reviews, and papers are distinct forms. The site labels each item so readers can understand the methods and claims appropriate to that work.</p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>Questions, corrections, source material, and article suggestions may be submitted through the <a href="{% url 'contact:form' %}">contact form</a>.</p>
</article>
{% endblock %}
</Layout>
